This paper deals with the formal definition and reasoning about variants of a modeling language, which is a topic that falls under the scope of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the semantics of language variants, which is related to logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on adapting a language to domain-specific needs is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
